<div class="siv-colcx-thinthickthin">
    <div class="parsys colcx"><div class="title section"><h1>State Departments</h1>
</div>
<div class="parbase textimage section">
<!-- BEGIN textimage -->

        
            
               
                <div class="image left">
            
            
        
        <img title="Organi dello Stato" alt="Organi dello Stato" class="cq-dd-image" src="/web/20131102165340im_/http://www.vaticanstate.va/content/vaticanstate/en/stato-e-governo/organi-dello-stato/_jcr_content/colcx/textimage/image.img.jpg/1361275151465.jpg"><div style="width:159px;"></div></div><div class="text"><p>Vatican City State is governed as an absolute monarchy. The Head of State is the Pope who holds full legislative, executive and judicial powers.<br>
During a sede vacante (between the death of a Pope and the election of his successor), these powers&nbsp; are exercised by the College of Cardinals.<br>
The Pope is elected by the Cardinals who are under eighty years of age. He becomes Sovereign of Vatican City State the moment he accepts his election as Pope.</p>
</div><br style="clear:both;"/><div class="clear"></div>
    <!-- END textimage --></div>
